docs.lead_paragraph: WATERLOO, Iowa, Aug. 6 (AP) -- Louise Suggs of Atlanta shot a two-under-par 70 today in the Waterloo Women's open golf tournament to move from fifth place to a tie for second with Mrs. Marlene Bauer Hagge of Delray Beach, Fla. Each had a three-round total of 214.

headline.main: MISS SUGGS ADVANCES; Her 70 Gains Second-Place Tie in Waterloo Golf

docs.lead_paragraph: The International Bank for Reconstruction and Development (World Bank) made thirty-one loans totaling $658,700,000 in the year ended on June 30, the bank announced yesterday. This compared with $703,000,000 the year before and brought the gross total of the bank's loan commitments on June 30 to $5,181,000,000.
